                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.515/560: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-10T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 10, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93. For Professor J. L. Buck from the Treasury. It will be most useful for you to
                    confer with Chinese Government officials and others with a view to informing
                    yourself most fully as to existing conditions and judgments in the economic
                    field, but please avoid such discussions of policy as might be construed to be
                    negotiations or representations of American official views.</p>
                <p>Please show this telegram to Nicholson, Treasury Attaché.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
